        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Chinese consumers drawn to secondhand shops as spending sputters Asia / Pacific Issued on: 06/03/2026 - 16:52 Surrounded by racks of used winter coats, sweaters and household appliances, Chinese shoppers browse items at a secondhand store in Shanghai looking for bargains. Green Cycle, the secondhand garment shop that shares a mall basement with three other sellers of used fashion, is part of a growing trend fed by budget-conscious shoppers amid slowing wage growth and a years-long property crisis in the world's second-largest economy. South Korean stock market plunges over potential Iran-related energy crisis 04/03/2026 Asia / Pacific A global superpower with a quiet voice: China 'not as loud or influential' beyond the Global South 04/03/2026 Asia / Pacific Death of Ali Khamenei : Pro-Iranian regime protesters attack US consulates 01/03/2026 Asia / Pacific 'Trump has a tradition of betraying his allies': Will Khamenei's death bring regime change in Iran? 01/03/2026 Asia / Pacific Why former Karabakh official Ruben Vardanyan isn't appealing his 20-year prison term in Azerbaijan 26/02/2026 Interview Asia / Pacific North Korea's Kim pledges economic push as his sister is elevated at party congress 25/02/2026 Asia / Pacific Pakistan launches border strikes on Afghanistan 22/02/2026 Asia / Pacific AI Summit in New Delhi, India: World leaders seek shared stance on AI 20/02/2026 Asia / Pacific India AI summit in New Delhi: When AI amplifies the biases of users 20/02/2026 Asia / Pacific"
